.TH "iscsi_host_alloc" 9 "iscsi_host_alloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
iscsi_host_alloc \- allocate a host and driver data
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct Scsi_Host *" iscsi_host_alloc
.BI "(struct scsi_host_template *sht "  ","
.BI "int dd_data_size "  ","
.BI "bool xmit_can_sleep "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sht" 12
scsi host template
.IP "dd_data_size" 12
driver host data size
.IP "xmit_can_sleep" 12
bool indicating if LLD will queue IO from a work queue
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This should be called by partial offload and software iscsi drivers.
To access the driver specific memory use the \fBiscsi_host_priv\fP macro.
